content.description: Thin start. Easier climbing to large jugs leads to a cool steep section involving a wedged baseball. Easier blocky climbing to the top. The whole roof looks like sketchy chert blocks, but is somehow all stuck together. The baseball moves a little but it's not going anywhere either.
content.protection: Maybe 8 bolts to lower-offs. Don't use your freshy red-point rope on this as the lower rubs your rope over some sharp edges. Feel free to rap.
content.location: This climb goes out the middle of the roof.

content.description: Follows a crystal seam to the right of a low flake. Mostly chert crimping. A nice warmup.
content.protection: Bolts. Originally was a mixed gear route but nobody was into it. Leaver biners at the anchor. Please don't toprope through them (also that would shred your rope).

content.description: Chert crimping. Tricky off the ground and then a thin crux midways. Watch out for the cactus in the upper corner.
content.protection: 7 or 8 bolts to chains. LO biners added.
content.location: Left of Smash and right of the roof route.

content.description: Very well bolted low angle corner with a steep finish.
content.location: Left most route on an arete.

content.description:
A ways left (200 yards) from the main amphitheater past the other routes. Four short routes with good rock quality. It also holds shade a bit later, perhaps 1 pm in the winter. The easiest routes at the Biscuit (but there's still cactus). 

  There's a fairly large bee hive perhaps 50 feet left of Canned Cranberry Sauce, about 10 feet off the ground. Pretty active Jan. 2019 but weren't bothering us.
